items.name: MachineLearning
items.description: A performant and dynamic MachineLearning framework written in .NET

items.name: Machine-Learning-and-Artificial-Intelligence-Exercises
items.description: Demonstrate the application of technical and analytical capabilities in Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). Utilize various tools and frameworks such as Python, Jupyter, Pandas, Seaborn, Plotly, PyTorch, and ChatGPT. Hands-on experience in Generative AI.

items.name: FEDOT
items.description: Automated modeling and machine learning framework FEDOT

items.name: aliad
items.description: Framework for anomaly detection with machine learning

items.name: Vishalvk2219
items.description: A collection of my projects that demonstrate my skills in AI, machine learning, web development, and data analysis. This repository includes various implementations and experiments, showcasing my expertise with tools like Python, React, Node.js, and deep learning frameworks.

items.name: SnapperML
items.description: SnapperML is a framework for machine learning. It has many functionalities including scalability through docker instances and reproducibility.

items.name: FreeCodeCamp_Machine_Learning-With_Python
items.description: Machine learning has many practical applications that you can use in your projects or on the job.  In the Machine Learning with Python Certification, you'll use the TensorFlow framework to build several neural networks and explore more advanced techniques like natural language processing and reinforcement learning.

items.name: linfa
items.description: A Rust machine learning framework.

items.name: News_Article_Summarization
items.description: Application that utilizes Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques and Machine Learning to automatically summarize news articles using Python, TensorFlow framework and Tkinter library.

items.name: House-Price-Prediction-using-Machine-Learning
items.description: I created a house price prediction system using Python for the core logic and Django for the user interface. The system leverages machine learning algorithms to predict property prices based on various features, and the Django framework provides a user-friendly web interface for easy interaction with the model.

items.name: secretflow
items.description: A unified framework for privacy-preserving data analysis and machine learning

items.name: IARE_Major_Project
items.description: Robust Machine Learning Framework for Detecting Diverse Application-Layer DDoS Attacks

items.name: IntelliAPI
items.description: IntelliAPI is a Django-based REST framework project designed to a simple REST API that makes machine learning models accessible through easy-to-use endpoints.

items.name: AgML
items.description: AgML is a centralized framework for agricultural machine learning. AgML provides access to public agricultural datasets for common agricultural deep learning tasks, with standard benchmarks and pretrained models, as well the ability to generate synthetic data and annotations.

items.name: MLJ.jl
items.description: A Julia machine learning framework

items.name: ReCell
items.description: ReCell is a Supervised Learning Framework (SLF) project focused on predicting the prices of used mobile devices. With the rise of the refurbished device market, ReCell leverages machine learning techniques to develop a dynamic pricing model.

items.name: Car_Price_Prediction
items.description: This is an end-to-end Machine Learning project based on the most recent vehicle dataset on CarDekho uses different data manipulation and visualization techniques for analysing the data. Model fitting is done using different regression techniques. And the Model is deployed using the Flask Framework.

items.name: ml-from-scratch
items.description: A comprehensive collection of practical machine learning examples using popular frameworks and libraries.

items.name: Machine_learning_framework
items.description: Machine learning tutorials

items.name: Heart-Attack-Model
items.description: This repository contains a machine learning project that predicts the likelihood of a heart attack based on a dataset of 170,501 rows and 25 features. The current model achieves an accuracy of 75%, with ongoing improvements through feature engineering and scaling.

items.name: MLOps-Template
items.description: Structured framework or project layout designed to streamline and standardize the development, deployment, and maintenance of machine learning (ML) projects.  It provides a foundation for implementing MLOps best practices and principles throughout the ML lifecycle.

items.name: FinanceCraft
items.description: FinanceCraft is a quantitative framework leveraging technical indicators and machine learning for stock market trend analysis and prediction.  It employs yfinance for data acquisition and Pandas for preprocessing, laying the groundwork for feature engineering, model training, and the implementation of trading algorithms.

items.name: DDoS-Detection-and-Mitigation-Framework-Using-Software-Defined-Networking-SDN-
items.description: Developed a real-time DDoS detection and mitigation system leveraging SDN's centralized control and machine learning algorithms. Implemented traffic analysis, feature extraction, and dynamic threat mitigation using tools like Mininet, Ryu Controller, and KNN.

items.name: mlpro
items.description: Learning materials for Mathematics for machine learning and Frameworks

items.name: silver-engine
items.description: Machine Learning Framework in C++

items.name: llm-finetuning-project
items.description: A lightweight framework for fine-tuning small language models, designed to run on basic hardware

items.name: pfund
items.description: An All-in-One Algo-Trading Framework: Backtest -> Train -> Trade -> Monitor. Machine / Deep Learning Ready. Supports All Trading: TradFi+CeFi+DeFi. Code Once, Trade Anywhere.
